How we can reproduce it?
From backtrace looks like that you have some non-installed debuginfo information..

Can you post outpu of: "rpm -q libsolv hawkey", please?
Does it crash everytime? Does it crash when you do "dnf clean all && dnf upgrade"?

Seems like it's dying in ret2e(), which can only deal with a very limited set of HY_E_ errors and asserts() if the error is unknown. ret=3 from the backtrace indicates HY_E_LIBSOLV, which is not handled.
This package has changed ownership in the Fedora Package Database. Reassigning to the new owner of this component.

The problematic part was replaced by libdnf that replaced hawkey for dnf-2.x. Therefore the problem should be solved. DNF-2.x is available for rawhide and Fedora 26, or can be downloaded from our testing repository ("dnf copr enable rpmsoftwaremanagement/dnf-nightly"). Please if the problem will reappeare with dnf-2.4.0 please, reopen the bug report.
